===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|玉|里|c1=s|c2=p|t1=jade|ls=psc}}.

According to ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'', the character meant “to polish jade”. The current meaning “to order, tidy up” may be derived from it.

===Etymology===
;"to cut jade, to mark out (field boundaries)"
:From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*b-rəj||draw, mark, boundary}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}); cognate with {{cog|apt|a-rí||boundary}}, {{cog|lus|ri||boundary, frontier, border}}, {{cog|duu|bri||to write}}, {{cog|mro|pri||to scratch}}, {{cog|bo|འབྲི||to write}}, {{cog|my|ရေး||to write}} & {{m|my|စာရေး||to write, clerk}}. Schuessler glossed its fundamental meaning as "cut in a regular way, divide into equal sections". See also {{och-l|筆|writing brush, pen}}, likely from [[allofam]]ic roots {{m|sit-pro|*b-ris||to draw; picture}} or {{m|sit-pro|*rit||to draw; boundary}}.

;"to regulate"
:STEDT groups this sense "to cut jade, to mark out (field boundaries)"; {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} noted that {{l-self|zh|理}} "to regulate" was often thought to be the same word as {{l-self|zh|理}} "to divide into sections", as the former sense might be derived from the latter.

;"to administer"
:Probably related to {{zh-l|釐|to regulate}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}})

;"envoy, jail official, matchmaker"
:Related to {{zh-l|吏|official}}, {{zh-l|史|scribe, historian}}, and {{zh-l|使|tr=shì|ambassador}}
:Possibly the same word as {{l-self|zh|理}} "to administer".
:According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, from {{der|zh|aav}}; compare {{cog|okz|re||to move, change position}} & its derivatives {{cog|okz|pre||to send, order, assign, appoint, delegate, use, employ, make}}, in turn related to {{m|okz|paṃre||to serve; service, duty; servant, delegate, representative, minister}}; with Sino-Tibetan causative *''s-'' corresponding to Khmer causative *''p-''..

